article.linkText: Golden scores 21 as Richmond defeats George Mason 65-50
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. -- Grant Golden had 21 points as Richmond topped George Mason 65-50 on Wednesday night. Blake Francis had 14 points for Richmond (20-6, 10-3 Atlantic 10 Conference), which earned its fifth straight win. Nathan Cayo added seven rebounds. Jordan Miller had 11 points and nine rebounds for the Patriots (14-12, 3-10). Javon Greene added 11 points. Greg Calixte had seven rebounds. The Spiders improve to 2-0 against the Patriots on the season. Richmond defeated George Mason 97-87 on Jan. 18. Richmond plays at St. Bonaventure on Saturday. George Mason plays Saint Joseph's at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com

videos.headline: Golden flushes putback slam for Richmond
videos.description: Richmond's Blake Francis is off the mark on his 3-pointer, but Grant Golden skies to grab the offensive rebound and slams it home with two hands.
